- Not quite, Andy.

107
00:11:59,618 --> 00:12:02,054
I haven't been out with Pamela Bucklin yet.

108
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:04,523
- Nobody's been out with her.

109
00:12:04,523 --> 00:12:05,324
- Nobody?

110
00:12:06,492 --> 00:12:09,728
- She's sweet 16 and never been kissed.

111
00:12:12,631 --> 00:12:13,466
- Never.

112
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,604
- Jerry Clark asked me out for a date today?

113
00:12:18,604 --> 00:12:19,872
- What'd you tell him?

114
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:21,607
- I told him I had to ask my father.

115
00:12:21,607 --> 00:12:23,642
- Yeah, you know how I feel about dating.

116
00:12:23,642 --> 00:12:25,411
- He just wants me to go to the game with him.

117
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:27,947
It's not really a date.

118
00:12:27,947 --> 00:12:29,348
He's a good Christian guy, dad

119
00:12:29,348 --> 00:12:32,318
probably the best Christian in the whole school.

120
00:12:32,318 --> 00:12:35,921
(students talking loudly)

121
00:12:45,831 --> 00:12:47,199
- Hey, how you doing?

122
00:12:47,199 --> 00:12:48,734
- Hi, Jerry.

123
00:12:48,734 --> 00:12:50,936
- So what's the good news we gonna go to the game?

124
00:12:50,936 --> 00:12:52,872
- Jerry, I think you're a great guy and everything,

125
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:54,874
but I can't go with you.

126
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:58,010
- Well, why not?

127
00:12:58,010 --> 00:12:59,745
- My father won't let me.

128
00:12:59,745 --> 00:13:01,280
- What do you mean your father won't let you?

129
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,815
I'm not asking you to marry me.

130
00:13:02,815 --> 00:13:04,750
I just want you to go to the game.

131
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:05,584
- I know.

132
00:13:06,485 --> 00:13:08,487
I'm sorry I can't go.

133
00:13:08,487 --> 00:13:10,923
- Look you said I was a great guy.

134
00:13:10,923 --> 00:13:12,525
Butter up your dad a little.

135
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:13,592
- I can't.

136
00:13:13,592 --> 00:13:15,728
He won't change his mind.

137
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:17,630
- Alright I get it.

138
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,198
I'm just not good enough for you.

139
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:21,200
- No, Jerry, that's not it at all.

140
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:25,638
My father won't let me go out with anybody I'm sorry.

141
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:27,439
- You don't have to make any excuses.

142
00:13:27,439 --> 00:13:28,941
I get the picture.

143
00:13:34,713 --> 00:13:36,148
- Are you crazy?

144
00:13:36,148 --> 00:13:37,950
I'd die if he asked me out.

145
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:39,418
I can't believe you said no.

146
00:13:39,418 --> 00:13:40,352
- My father won't let me.

147
00:13:40,352 --> 00:13:41,954
What else was I supposed to say?

148
00:13:41,954 --> 00:13:43,389
- What's wrong with your dad, Pam?

149
00:13:43,389 --> 00:13:45,357
He won't let you go out with anybody.

150
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:47,259
My father let's me go out with whoever I want

151
00:13:47,259 --> 00:13:48,694
as long as he's a Christian.

152
00:13:48,694 --> 00:13:50,129
- Well, he wants me to wait for the Lord

153
00:13:50,129 --> 00:13:51,630
to bring the right guy along.

154
00:13:51,630 --> 00:13:53,566
- But how are you supposed to know who the right guy is

155
00:13:53,566 --> 00:13:56,135
if you never go out with anybody?

156
00:13:56,135 --> 00:13:57,770
- How am I supposed to know who the right guy is

157
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:59,572
if I never go out with anybody?

158
00:13:59,572 --> 00:14:01,173
- Pamela, who've you been talking to?

159
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:02,341
- Doesn't make sense, dad.

160
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,642
I don't see why I can't go out with a guy.

161
00:14:03,642 --> 00:14:04,877
Nothing's gonna happen.

162
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:06,912
- I've told you why I don't want you to date.

163
00:14:06,912 --> 00:14:08,581
- Dad, I'm wanna get married someday.

164
00:14:08,581 --> 00:14:10,649
I don't wanna be single my whole life.

165
00:14:10,649 --> 00:14:13,552
- (laughing) You just turned 16.

166
00:14:13,552 --> 00:14:15,854
You'll probably be married before any of your girlfriends.

167
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:16,889
- I doubt it.

168
00:14:16,889 --> 00:14:18,490
- Look I know it's hard.

169
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:20,693
All your friends are dating and you're not,

170
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:24,630
but it's for your own protection just trust me.

171
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:29,335
- So what kind of a guy does your dad want you to marry?

172
00:14:29,335 --> 00:14:31,904
- He wants me to marry a guy who's never kissed a girl.

173
00:14:31,904 --> 00:14:33,405
- He what?

174
00:14:33,405 --> 00:14:34,940
- He wants me to marry a guy who's never kissed a girl.

175
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:35,908
- You're kidding.

176
00:14:35,908 --> 00:14:37,409
- Nope.

177
00:14:37,409 --> 00:14:39,278
- Pam, your dad wants you to marry a guy who doesn't exist.

178
00:14:39,278 --> 00:14:40,946
- He thinks he does.

179
00:14:41,981 --> 00:14:43,515
- So why won't he let you date?

180
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:45,251
- He wants me to remain pure.

181
00:14:45,251 --> 00:14:47,086
He doesn't want me to be tempted to kiss anyone

182
00:14:47,086 --> 00:14:48,520
until my wedding day.

183
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:50,422
- Wait a minute your dad wants you to wait

184
00:14:50,422 --> 00:14:52,091
until your wedding day to kiss a guy,

185
00:14:52,091 --> 00:14:53,325
and he wants your husband to wait

186
00:14:53,325 --> 00:14:54,727
until his wedding day to kiss a girl.

187
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:55,995
- That's right.

188
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:58,063
Jessica, please don't repeat that to anyone.

189
00:14:58,063 --> 00:15:00,099
Everybody thinks I'm weird enough as it is.

190
00:15:00,099 --> 00:15:02,568
- Don't worry I won't.

191
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:03,969
Pam, I like your dad and everything

192
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:06,605
but he's living in a dream world.

193
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:07,773
What's his thing about kissing?

194
00:15:07,773 --> 00:15:09,808
I've kissed guys before and I feel bad.

195
00:15:09,808 --> 00:15:12,911
Kissing's fun you're really missing out.

196
00:15:12,911 --> 00:15:14,980
- Jessica's father lets her go out with guys

197
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:16,682
as long as they're Christians.

198
00:15:16,682 --> 00:15:20,319
- I wonder what Jessica's husband would say if he knew that?

199
00:15:20,319 --> 00:15:22,154
- What do you mean?

200
00:15:22,154 --> 00:15:24,890
- Pamela, whenever we come to a point in our lives

201
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:26,558
when we're not sure what to do,

202
00:15:26,558 --> 00:15:27,960
we should always look ahead

203
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:30,195
and view things from that perspective.

204
00:15:30,195 --> 00:15:32,698
For example, in your case about dating

205
00:15:32,698 --> 00:15:34,767
let's look ahead to your wedding day.

206
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,001
You'll be getting married to the

207
00:15:36,001 --> 00:15:38,037
man you love with all your heart.

208
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:39,171
This is the man you're going to spend

209
00:15:39,171 --> 00:15:41,640
the rest of your life with.

210
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:45,978
Now let's go ahead a little further to your wedding night.

211
00:15:45,978 --> 00:15:48,380
When you lie down on your wedding bed,

212
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:51,250
what kind of a man do you want your husband to be?

213
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:54,486
Do you wanna man who saved all his love just for you

214
00:15:54,486 --> 00:15:56,755
one who never even kissed another woman

215
00:15:56,755 --> 00:15:59,391
so he could share that just with you,

216
00:15:59,391 --> 00:16:02,361
or do you want a man who's been with other women before

217
00:16:02,361 --> 00:16:05,597
one who kissed other women and didn't wait for you?

218
00:16:05,597 --> 00:16:08,667
Which one would you prefer?

219
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:11,603
- I prefer the one who waited.

220
00:16:11,603 --> 00:16:13,939
- And so would your husband.

221
00:16:17,743 --> 00:16:18,844
- Hi, Pam.

222
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:20,079
- Hi, Jerry. - How you doing?

223
00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:22,014
- I'm doing okay.

224
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:23,248
- The game's tomorrow night,

225
00:16:23,248 --> 00:16:24,350
and I'm still not going with anybody.

226
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:26,051
Did your father change his mind?

227
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:28,187
- No, he didn't sorry.

228
00:16:28,187 --> 00:16:29,688
- I'd really like to go with you.

229
00:16:29,688 --> 00:16:32,424
Maybe we could meet and sit together just as friends?

230
00:16:32,424 --> 00:16:36,328
- I'd like that, Jerry, I really would but I can't.

231
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:37,529
- You know I think it's great and all

232
00:16:37,529 --> 00:16:40,432
you respect your father I really do,

233
00:16:40,432 --> 00:16:43,168
but you're not a little girl anymore.

234
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:44,002
See ya.

235
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:49,108
(dramatic music)

236
00:17:11,597 --> 00:17:14,333
(dramatic music)

237
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:35,387
- Hi, Pam. - Hi.

238
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:42,928
- Lots of kids are laughing at me

239
00:17:42,928 --> 00:17:45,164
because of your old fashioned ways.

240
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:47,332
- There's nothing old fashioned about purity.

241
00:17:47,332 --> 00:17:49,301
- You can't show me one verse in the bible

242
00:17:49,301 --> 00:17:51,336
where it says it's wrong to date.

243
00:17:51,336 --> 00:17:52,905
- Pamela, what's gotten into you?

244
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:55,707
- Nothing it's just I'm not a little girl anymore.

245
00:17:55,707 --> 00:17:58,076
- I know that, but I'm still your father

246
00:17:58,076 --> 00:18:00,079
and I'm responsible for your well being.

247
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:01,747
- You don't trust me that's what it is.

248
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:02,848
You don't trust me.

249
00:18:02,848 --> 00:18:04,616
- I trust you very much.

250
00:18:04,616 --> 00:18:06,952
- Then why won't you let me go to the game with Jerry?

251
00:18:06,952 --> 00:18:09,221
- Because it's against my better judgment.

252
00:18:09,221 --> 00:18:10,923
- But you're making my life miserable, dad.

253
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,091
Don't you see that you're making it miserable?

254
00:18:13,091 --> 00:18:13,926
- Pamela,

255
00:18:14,793 --> 00:18:15,861
Pamela.

256
00:18:15,861 --> 00:18:18,630
(door slamming)

257
00:18:32,544 --> 00:18:33,779
(soft knocking)

258
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:34,613
Pamela,

259
00:18:35,681 --> 00:18:37,149
(soft knocking)

260
00:18:37,149 --> 00:18:39,017
Pamela, may I come in it's time to pray?

261
00:18:39,017 --> 00:18:42,488
- I've already said my prayers good night.

262
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:43,689
- [Wayne] I've prayed with you every night

263
00:18:43,689 --> 00:18:44,857
since the day you were born.

264
00:18:44,857 --> 00:18:45,791
- Good night.

265
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:47,626
- Pamela. - Good night.

266
00:18:52,164 --> 00:18:54,900
- [Wayne] Dear Lord, we love you.

267
00:18:56,335 --> 00:18:59,004
Thank you for this day.

268
00:18:59,004 --> 00:19:01,039
Please watch over Pamela.

269
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:05,878
Help me to be the father you want me to be

270
00:19:05,878 --> 00:19:07,546
in Jesus' name amen.

271
00:19:10,782 --> 00:19:12,384
Good night, Pamela.

272
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:26,832
(dramatic music)

273
00:19:53,191 --> 00:19:56,261
(telephone ringing)

274
00:19:58,630 --> 00:20:00,732
Christian Film Library this is Wayne.

275
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:01,800
- Hey, dad.

276
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,435
- Pamela, hi.

277
00:20:03,435 --> 00:20:04,803
- Dad, I'm going to the game a little early tonight

278
00:20:04,803 --> 00:20:06,138
so I won't be home for supper.

279
00:20:06,138 --> 00:20:08,173
I've got yours ready though it's in the oven.

280
00:20:08,173 --> 00:20:09,241
- Alright thanks.

281
00:20:09,241 --> 00:20:10,542
Who you going with?

282
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:12,744
- I'm going with Jessica.

283
00:20:12,744 --> 00:20:14,813
- Okay, be home on time.

284
00:20:14,813 --> 00:20:17,049
- I will, dad, love ya bye.

285
00:20:17,983 --> 00:20:18,817
- Bye.

286
00:20:27,459 --> 00:20:30,395
(crowd screaming)

287
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:35,234
(cheerleaders cheering)

288
00:20:46,011 --> 00:20:49,548
(crowd chanting)

289
00:20:49,548 --> 00:20:52,384
(dramatic music)

290
00:21:37,162 --> 00:21:38,897
- I'd better go on from here.

291
00:21:38,897 --> 00:21:40,365
- Is everything okay?

292
00:21:40,365 --> 00:21:44,069
- Yeah, it's just my dad he's a little over protective.

293
00:21:44,069 --> 00:21:46,371
You understand? - Yeah.

294
00:21:46,371 --> 00:21:49,775
But what's your hurry it's not very late.

295
00:21:51,276 --> 00:21:53,845
(tense music)

296
00:22:11,196 --> 00:22:13,765
(tense music)

297
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:57,642
- Sorry I'm late.

298
00:23:00,412 --> 00:23:03,882
(students talking loudly)

299
00:23:09,988 --> 00:23:11,289
- So how was it?

300
00:23:11,289 --> 00:23:14,025
- Jessica, why is everybody looking at me?

301
00:23:14,025 --> 00:23:15,393
- Probably because the whole school knows

302
00:23:15,393 --> 00:23:16,695
about you and Jerry?

303
00:23:16,695 --> 00:23:17,729
So what'd you think of kissing?

304
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:18,630
Did you like it?

305
00:23:18,630 --> 00:23:19,664
- I didn't kiss him.

306
00:23:19,664 --> 00:23:20,532
- That's not what I heard.

307
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:21,933
- What did you hear?

308
00:23:21,933 --> 00:23:23,201
- Well, I heard that you and Jerry

309
00:23:23,201 --> 00:23:24,870
made out for a while in the living room.

310
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:25,871
- That's not true.

311
00:23:25,871 --> 00:23:27,339
Who'd you hear that from?

312
00:23:27,339 --> 00:23:29,508
- Well, Mitzy told me and she heard it from Andy

313
00:23:29,508 --> 00:23:31,576
and he probably heard it from Jerry.

314
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:32,811
- Jerry's lying.

315
00:23:32,811 --> 00:23:34,446
He tried to kiss me but I didn't let him.

316
00:23:34,446 --> 00:23:36,748
He didn't even come into my house.

317
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:39,184
- That's not what's going around.

318
00:23:39,184 --> 00:23:42,354
- So Jerry told everyone he kissed you.

319
00:23:42,354 --> 00:23:45,157
- He didn't, dad, why is he saying that?

320
00:23:45,157 --> 00:23:46,525
- Well, first of all

321
00:23:46,525 --> 00:23:49,060
maybe the Lord's trying to teach you a lesson.

322
00:23:49,060 --> 00:23:51,463
If had obeyed your father, none of this would've happened.

323
00:23:51,463 --> 00:23:52,297
- I know.

324
00:23:53,131 --> 00:23:54,866
- You also deceived me.

325
00:23:54,866 --> 00:23:56,768
You said you were going to the game with Jessica

326
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:59,471
which you did but you met Jerry there.

327
00:23:59,471 --> 00:24:01,740
Now Jerry's telling everyone he went out with you

328
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:05,043
which he did but what happened is another story.

329
00:24:05,043 --> 00:24:06,711
- I don't know why I did it.

330
00:24:06,711 --> 00:24:09,915
All the other girls were going on dates and I wasn't.

331
00:24:09,915 --> 00:24:13,518
- Pamela, I would never ever do anything to hurt you.

332
00:24:13,518 --> 00:24:15,187
I love you.

333
00:24:15,187 --> 00:24:17,522
- I know, dad, and I'm really sorry.

334
00:24:17,522 --> 00:24:19,758
I'll never do anything like this again.

335
00:24:19,758 --> 00:24:21,259
Please forgive me.

336
00:24:22,427 --> 00:24:23,762
- I forgive you.

337
00:24:24,863 --> 00:24:26,665
- I love you, dad.

338
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:27,899
- Love you too.

339
00:24:29,334 --> 00:24:32,671
Pamela, a kiss is something you shouldn't just give away.

340
00:24:32,671 --> 00:24:34,673
It's very special.

341
00:24:34,673 --> 00:24:36,741
What does the minister say just after he's

342
00:24:36,741 --> 00:24:38,977
pronounced the couple husband and wife?

343
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:41,980
He says, "You may now kiss bride."

344
00:24:44,883 --> 00:24:46,485
Please keep out any root of bitterness

345
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:48,753
from springing up in our hearts.

346
00:24:48,753 --> 00:24:50,722
Help us not to be angry.

347
00:24:50,722 --> 00:24:54,426
We pray for Jerry and ask that you would work in his life.

348
00:24:54,426 --> 00:24:57,462
Thank you for what you're teaching us in this situation

349
00:24:57,462 --> 00:24:59,130
in Jesus' name amen.

350
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:01,499
- Amen.

351
00:25:01,499 --> 00:25:02,734
Thanks, dad.

352
00:25:02,734 --> 00:25:04,269
- Your welcome.

353
00:25:04,269 --> 00:25:08,640
- Dad, I never thought Jerry would spread a lie about me.

354
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,375
- People lie to cover themselves.

355
00:25:10,375 --> 00:25:12,143
Maybe Jerry did some bragging to his buddies,

356
00:25:12,143 --> 00:25:15,814
and now he has to live up to it by lying I don't know.

357
00:25:15,814 --> 00:25:18,950
- What can I do everybody thinks I did something I didn't?

358
00:25:18,950 --> 00:25:20,886
- You could transfer to another school.

359
00:25:20,886 --> 00:25:21,720
- I wish.

360
00:25:22,888 --> 00:25:26,057
- Or you could do what Jesus did.

361
00:25:26,057 --> 00:25:27,826
Remember when he stood in front of Pilate

362
00:25:27,826 --> 00:25:29,494
and they falsely accused him?

363
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:31,429
He didn't say anything.

364
00:25:31,429 --> 00:25:34,399
Jesus didn't defend himself against the lies,

365
00:25:34,399 --> 00:25:36,268
and Pilate was amazed.

366
00:25:36,268 --> 00:25:37,769
You know why?

367
00:25:37,769 --> 00:25:40,338
Because he saw the humble reaction of Christ,

368
00:25:40,338 --> 00:25:42,741
and it showed him who was really lying.

369
00:25:42,741 --> 00:25:44,309
Well, you could do the same.

370
00:25:44,309 --> 00:25:47,846
Don't say anything, don't defend yourself, don't get upset.

371
00:25:47,846 --> 00:25:49,948
Just be patient and let the Lord

372
00:25:49,948 --> 00:25:52,450
have control of the situation.

373
00:26:16,574 --> 00:26:17,809
- [Andy] Hi, Pam.

374
00:26:17,809 --> 00:26:18,710
- Hi, Andy.

375
00:26:19,778 --> 00:26:21,279
- Pam, I was just wondering

376
00:26:21,279 --> 00:26:24,149
if you'd like to go to the game with me this Friday night?

377
00:26:24,149 --> 00:26:26,351
- No, I can't thanks anyway.

378
00:26:26,351 --> 00:26:27,919
- Are you going out with Jerry again?

379
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:32,090
- No, I'm not going out with Jerry and he didn't...

380
00:26:35,493 --> 00:26:38,496
No, I'm not going out with anybody.

381
00:26:38,496 --> 00:26:41,333
(dramatic music)

382
00:27:10,495 --> 00:27:13,064
- But I would not have you to be ignorant, brethren,

383
00:27:13,064 --> 00:27:15,166
concerning them which are asleep.

384
00:27:15,166 --> 00:27:19,571
That ye sorrow not even as others which have no hope.

385
00:27:19,571 --> 00:27:22,440
For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again,

386
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:25,210
even so them also which sleep in Jesus

387
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:27,545
will God bring with him.

388
00:27:27,545 --> 00:27:30,448
For this we say unto you by the word of the Lord

389
00:27:30,448 --> 00:27:32,017
that we which are alive and remain

390
00:27:32,017 --> 00:27:33,685
until the coming of the Lord

391
00:27:33,685 --> 00:27:36,488
shall not prevent them which are asleep.

392
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:39,724
For the Lord himself shall descend from Heaven with a shout

393
00:27:39,724 --> 00:27:43,862
with the voice of the archangel and with the trump of God.

394
00:27:43,862 --> 00:27:46,898
The dead in Christ shall rise first.

395
00:27:46,898 --> 00:27:48,667
Then we which are alive and remain

396
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:51,703
shall be caught up together with them in the clouds

397
00:27:51,703 --> 00:27:53,972
to meet the Lord in the air

398
00:27:53,972 --> 00:27:56,841
and so shall we ever be with the Lord.

399
00:27:56,841 --> 00:28:00,712
Wherefore comfort one another with these words.

400
00:28:05,617 --> 00:28:09,287
(students speaking loudly)

401
00:28:18,730 --> 00:28:22,333
Do you know what a Christian Film Library is, Fredric?

402
00:28:22,333 --> 00:28:25,270
- It's got something to do with Christian films, right?

403
00:28:25,270 --> 00:28:26,504
- Right.

404
00:28:26,504 --> 00:28:28,773
We distribute films to churches, schools,

405
00:28:28,773 --> 00:28:32,110
and other groups interested in spreading the gospel.

406
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:35,713
My father started the library back in 1945

407
00:28:35,713 --> 00:28:39,250
but he just went to be with the Lord last month.

408
00:28:39,250 --> 00:28:40,552
Pamela's been coming in after school

409
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:42,253
helping with the book work.

410
00:28:42,253 --> 00:28:45,290
Now I need someone back here to help with the films.

411
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:47,058
The job would be every day after school

412
00:28:47,058 --> 00:28:48,626
for about three hours.

413
00:28:48,626 --> 00:28:49,994
Would that work in your schedule?

414
00:28:49,994 --> 00:28:51,863
- Yes, sir that'd be good.

415
00:28:51,863 --> 00:28:53,364
- All right.

416
00:28:53,364 --> 00:28:55,467
Well, why don't you tell me something about yourself.

417
00:28:55,467 --> 00:28:57,068
Pamela says you're new in school.

418
00:28:57,068 --> 00:28:58,236
- That's right, sir, we just moved here

419
00:28:58,236 --> 00:29:00,105
this summer from Seattle.

420
00:29:00,105 --> 00:29:02,107
Let's see I'm a senior,

421
00:29:02,107 --> 00:29:05,009
and I became a Christian when I was nine years old.

422
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:06,578
I've been wanting to work in a ministry,

423
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:08,113
and when I saw your sign at school,

424
00:29:08,113 --> 00:29:10,048
it looked like a good opportunity.

425
00:29:10,048 --> 00:29:11,883
I don't know much about film libraries,

426
00:29:11,883 --> 00:29:13,284
but I'm willing to learn.

427
00:29:13,284 --> 00:29:14,519
Promise to work real hard

428
00:29:14,519 --> 00:29:16,955
and try to do the best job I can.

429
00:29:18,156 --> 00:29:20,525
- You think you'd like to work here, Fredric?

430
00:29:20,525 --> 00:29:23,194
- Yes, I'd like to give it a try.

431
00:29:23,194 --> 00:29:25,697
(soft music)

432
00:30:12,844 --> 00:30:14,812
- Ready to watch the film?

433
00:30:14,812 --> 00:30:16,881
- Nah, I don't feel like it tonight.

434
00:30:16,881 --> 00:30:20,218
- It's a new release just came in today.

435
00:30:21,186 --> 00:30:23,855
Where's Jessica tonight?

436
00:30:23,855 --> 00:30:26,424
- She's out with her boyfriend.

437
00:30:28,293 --> 00:30:29,227
- Should be a great film.

438
00:30:29,227 --> 00:30:31,896
Why don't you watch it with me?

439
00:30:31,896 --> 00:30:32,964
- No, thanks.

440
00:30:54,919 --> 00:30:56,187
- Hi, Jessica, come on in.

441
00:30:56,187 --> 00:30:57,689
- Hi, Mr. Bucklin.

442
00:30:58,856 --> 00:30:59,824
Is Pam home?

443
00:30:59,824 --> 00:31:00,692
- Yeah, she's up in her room.

444
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:01,526
- Thanks.

445
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:05,029
- Jessica, are you alright?

446
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:06,864
- Yeah.

447
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:11,469
(dramatic music)

448
00:31:11,469 --> 00:31:13,104
Last night we went out for pizza

449
00:31:13,104 --> 00:31:15,673
and then we took a drive.

450
00:31:15,673 --> 00:31:19,010
We stopped and parked and then we made out

451
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:20,712
and it was great.

452
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:23,915
(dramatic music)

453
00:31:23,915 --> 00:31:26,517
Then he said our relationship had reached a turning point

454
00:31:26,517 --> 00:31:30,688
and that if we really loved each other we should...

455
00:31:32,557 --> 00:31:34,892
I can't believe it happened.

456
00:31:36,661 --> 00:31:37,895
If I would've said no,

457
00:31:37,895 --> 00:31:41,499
he would've thought that I didn't love him.

458
00:31:45,370 --> 00:31:49,540
I should've known better after what he did to you.

459
00:31:52,844 --> 00:31:54,245
I feel so guilty.

460
00:31:56,281 --> 00:31:57,849
What am I gonna do?

461
00:32:14,365 --> 00:32:15,199
- Dad,

462
00:32:16,801 --> 00:32:19,003
I need to talk to you about something.

463
00:32:19,003 --> 00:32:20,738
- What is it, Pamela?

464
00:32:22,507 --> 00:32:23,341
Pamela.

465
00:32:24,642 --> 00:32:27,445
- Something bad happened to Jessica last night.

466
00:32:27,445 --> 00:32:28,780
- What happened?

467
00:32:31,015 --> 00:32:32,283
Pamela.

468
00:32:32,283 --> 00:32:33,818
- She just wanted Jerry to love her dad.

469
00:32:33,818 --> 00:32:35,920
She didn't mean for anything to happen.

470
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:38,323
- What are you talking about?

471
00:32:39,457 --> 00:32:40,291
- Jessica

472
00:32:43,628 --> 00:32:45,963
went out with her boyfriend.

473
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:51,636
(dramatic music)

474
00:33:06,751 --> 00:33:09,187
She came to me for help today,

475
00:33:09,187 --> 00:33:12,323
but I didn't know what to say.

476
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:14,525
She feels so guilty.

477
00:33:14,525 --> 00:33:16,694
She won't forgive herself.

478
00:33:18,262 --> 00:33:19,931
What can I tell her?

479
00:33:21,265 --> 00:33:23,368
Dad, what can I tell her?

480
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:28,940
- The Pharisees brought a woman

481
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:32,910
caught in the act of adultery to Jesus.

482
00:33:32,910 --> 00:33:36,514
They said, "The law of Moses says to stone her.

483
00:33:36,514 --> 00:33:38,483
"What do you say?"

484
00:33:38,483 --> 00:33:41,152
Jesus knew what they were up to.

485
00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:43,821
He said, "He who is without sin

486
00:33:43,821 --> 00:33:46,557
"let him cast the first stone."

487
00:33:46,557 --> 00:33:50,862
One by one they all left just the woman remained.

488
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:52,764
Jesus said to her,

489
00:33:52,764 --> 00:33:54,832
"Did anyone condemn you?"

490
00:33:54,832 --> 00:33:57,201
She said, "No one, Lord."

491
00:33:57,201 --> 00:33:59,203
He said, "Neither do I",

492
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:03,775
but then he gave her a command.

493
00:34:05,042 --> 00:34:07,145
- "Go and sin no more."

494
00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:14,318
- Be with Jessica tonight, Lord

495
00:34:14,318 --> 00:34:16,154
comfort her, heal her,

496
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:20,124
draw her close to you

497
00:34:20,124 --> 00:34:21,793
in Jesus' name amen.

498
00:34:23,227 --> 00:34:24,896
- Amen.

499
00:34:24,896 --> 00:34:25,830
Thanks, dad.

500
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:27,698
- You're welcome good night.

501
00:34:27,698 --> 00:34:28,699
- Night dad.

502
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:33,905
- Pamela,

503
00:34:34,806 --> 00:34:36,174
- Yes, dad.

504
00:34:36,174 --> 00:34:38,643
- You mentioned a boy's name tonight, Jerry

505
00:34:38,643 --> 00:34:40,778
is that Jerry Clark?

506
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:41,712
- Yes, dad.

507
00:34:44,215 --> 00:34:45,283
- Good night.

508
00:34:47,251 --> 00:34:48,085
- Night.

509
00:34:52,356 --> 00:34:54,392
- Our records show it went out on Monday, John.

510
00:34:54,392 --> 00:34:57,128
It should've been there the next day.

511
00:34:57,128 --> 00:34:59,831
Yes, but I can't run a tracer at 6:00 p.m. on Friday.

512
00:34:59,831 --> 00:35:02,533
You needed to call me earlier at least yesterday

513
00:35:02,533 --> 00:35:06,237
then I could've gotten another one to you.

514
00:35:06,237 --> 00:35:10,708
Not unless you can come down and pick one up.

515
00:35:10,708 --> 00:35:12,477
I'm very sorry, John.

516
00:35:13,711 --> 00:35:14,545
Right.

517
00:35:16,047 --> 00:35:17,715
- What happened Mr. Bucklin?

518
00:35:17,715 --> 00:35:20,218
- Faith Community didn't get their film for tonight.

519
00:35:20,218 --> 00:35:22,386
They're having a big youth rally that starts at eight.

520
00:35:22,386 --> 00:35:24,255
It's about two hours from here.

521
00:35:24,255 --> 00:35:26,090
- I know I shipped it out on Monday.

522
00:35:26,090 --> 00:35:27,859
- It's not your fault, Fredric.

523
00:35:27,859 --> 00:35:30,495
Every once in a while something like this happens.

524
00:35:30,495 --> 00:35:32,930
I do whatever I can to go the films there

525
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:35,099
but there's not much I can do about it tonight.

526
00:35:35,099 --> 00:35:36,567
It's my mother's birthday.

527
00:35:36,567 --> 00:35:38,069
Pamela's cooking a big dinner.

528
00:35:38,069 --> 00:35:39,837
In fact I'm late now.

529
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:44,142
- Well, I'm really sorry about the film, sir.

530
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:45,510
- Yeah, I am too.

531
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:46,844
Look do you mind locking up for me?

532
00:35:46,844 --> 00:35:48,112
- No, not at all.

533
00:35:48,112 --> 00:35:48,946
- I'll be through in about five minutes.

534
00:35:48,946 --> 00:35:49,780
- Thanks.

535
00:35:50,815 --> 00:35:52,183
Have a good weekend, Fredric.

536
00:35:52,183 --> 00:35:53,417
